Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with Red Hat. I bring over three years of professional experience in systems programming, automation, and distributed systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an MCP AI interaction layer that validates natural-language intents into safe, tested tool calls across 1,000+ endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed systems. To keep these systems production-ready, I built automation scripts and code-generation solutions for API integration, accelerating developer onboarding and improving implementation correctness. I also designed a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using Python, LangChain, and LangGraph, enabling scalable tool execution with automated testing and CI/CD pipelines — reducing latency by 60% through targeted automation and performance optimization. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that seamlessly handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via signed URLs — giving me direct, hands-on experience with multi-environment backend design and Linux systems. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with enterprise-grade reliability through automated testing and CI/CD, and developed backend automation workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running jobs and prevent Lambda timeouts for distributed systems. Together, these roles have prepared me to write and implement code in C, Python, and Go, troubleshoot and debug complex systems, build smart automation, and collaborate with senior engineers to ship enterprise-grade code that works for customers.

